3. Trieste provisions, in agreement with Yugoslavia, accompanied by
                                mutual Italian-Yugoslav assurances that with a settlement there
                                would be no outstanding territorial questions between them;

5. revision of those clauses covering Italy’s international
                                commitments and commitments to specific countries (Articles 24
                                through 44);
